text:
found this useful thought others would too: 

If you run into the google chrome inspector bug where the body element is collapsed and cannot be expanded, `alt`+`r` will refresh just the inspector window, often fixing the issue.

I run into this bug all the time and it’s frustrating.
I thought I was the only one experiencing this! Thank you for posting this

I thought I was in the minority experiencing that annoying bug. lol I reported it on the chrome bug reporter like 4 weeks ago and haven’t seen it get fixed in canary or anything so I thought maybe I’m an edge case. I have people at my office who haven’t experienced it yet. evidently I’m not if 6 of you have the same issue
